post_text:
Parents and Guardians,
As we navigate through COVID and coming back to school, I would like to clarify some things. When we have a positive case we will be in contact only with those affected. If you do not hear from the administration, plan on attending school as regularly scheduled. Please watch email, Facebook, and our website calendar for any activities that are being cancelled or rescheduled. This is new for all of us and we are trying our best with the regulations we must follow. We do not make decisions based on rumors, but rather facts. We work directly with each family and each case has a different set of circumstances. Our decisions are in consultation with the Palo Alto County Public Health Department. Thank you for your understanding during these unusual times.

Amanda Schmidt, Superintendent

West Bend-Mallard School will be starting school Face to Face beginning Monday, August 24th for PreK-12th grades. This will be everyday all day, unless COVID numbers would start to rise. It seems like there has been some confusion so I wanted to make sure everyone understood. For more details, please refer to our website at www.west-bend.k12.ia.us under the COVID tab. Please feel free to contact me with any questions.

Amanda Schmidt
515-887-7821
schmidt@west-bend.k12.ia.us

Parents and Families,

The State of Iowa would like to ask you about technology access for your household. This information will help in planning for next school year, should learning from home need to occur because of the COVID-19 pandemic. Our district encourages you to complete this survey so your technology barriers are known to the State.

• The survey should take less than five minutes to complete.
•Please check your email to find the survey.

*DRIVERS EDUCATION* With things constantly changing due to COVID-19 we are not 100% positive what Drivers Ed will look like this summer. However, for us to start planning we need to get a list of students who are going to take Drivers Ed with us this summer. Your student needs to be 14 at the time class begins and have their learners permit.

Our goal is to complete Drivers Ed as soon as possible and allow students to have their school permits by the time fall sports begin. If you have any questions please let me know, email is probably the best way to get ahold of me.

You can sign your student up for Drivers Ed by emailing Mr. Peppmeier at ppeppmeier@west-bend.k12.ia.us or calling the school at 515-887-7821.

post_text:
WBM Food Pantry UPDATE:
*Change of Days this week*. The food pantry will be open TUESDAY (4/7/20) and WEDNESDAY (4/8/20) from 3:00pm-6:00pm. There will be no Friday pantry because of Good Friday.
In order to follow social distancing and limiting any large groups in the kitchen, we will have food items pre-packaged for families if they come in. Please DO NOT bring more than 1 other person with you and if you are feeling sick DO NOT COME to the school, call 887-4523 and we will make arrangements to get something to you.

Weather and help permitting-if we are able we will meet people outside with the items to put in their trunks to help limit contact. This is a "learning curve" for us, so Thank You for being patient! WE ARE IN THIS TOGETHER #WolverineCountry

post_text:
We are going to try to do the food pantry every Tuesday and Friday afternoon 4-6pm. Open to any one in the WBM school district with children in the school for as long as we have food available.
You may come once a week, in order to comply with social distancing PLEASE only 1 or 2 people for your family to come in so we don't have a lot of people. If you can leave smaller children at home that would be best.
If you are feeling sick PLEASE DO NOT COME TO THE SCHOOL. Call 887-4523 and we will deliver something to your home within a 10 mile radius of WB, we will go to Mallard if needed.
Entrance is back of the school by the girls locker rooms. Use hand sanitizer provided when you come in.
We're here for you!

post_text: During the COVID-19 outbreak our medical facilities are in an extreme shortage of facemasks and we could help by making reusable ones. We are reaching out to any student who would be willing to sew facemasks for healthcare facilities. You would need to have a sewing machine at home to complete this project. If you are interested in helping sew, please email Mrs. Peppmeier and she will get you the directions. If Mrs. Peppmeier gets a response of people that want to help, she will put together some supplies that can be picked up in the Admin building between 10 and 2 Monday, Tuesday or Wednesday.
